WEBVTT

00:12.041 --> 00:13.959
[Ray]
Previously on  Ray Donovan...

00:13.959 --> 00:16.500
I know you want me.
I know you want to be with me.

00:16.500 --> 00:17.959
You out of
your fucking mind?

00:17.959 --> 00:19.834
- You followed me?
- Fucking right I did.

00:19.834 --> 00:21.333
She's gonna tell Dad.

00:21.333 --> 00:22.792
If she does,
he'll kill him.

00:22.792 --> 00:24.125
And maybe he deserves it?

00:24.125 --> 00:25.709
If anyone lays a hand
on him,

00:25.709 --> 00:27.125
you will never fucking
see me again.

00:29.792 --> 00:31.959
That did not happen.

00:31.959 --> 00:34.417
- I ain't fucking senile.
- Fine. You're not senile.

00:34.417 --> 00:36.125
Go tell Joe Friday out there
that you want to wear a wire

00:36.125 --> 00:38.458
and get your brains
blown out in Long Beach.

00:38.458 --> 00:41.250
You want out?

00:41.250 --> 00:42.333
There is no out.

00:42.333 --> 00:43.667
Ow!

00:43.667 --> 00:45.458
[grunts]

00:45.458 --> 00:47.291
[Ray]
You got to leave L.A.

00:47.291 --> 00:48.375
[Mickey] You tricked
their beloved grandfather

00:48.375 --> 00:50.333
into signing away his rights,

00:50.333 --> 00:52.041
or you're the kind of son that
dumps his demented old man

00:52.041 --> 00:53.542
in a nursing home.

00:53.542 --> 00:56.041
Either way...
they're gonna hate ya.

00:57.458 --> 00:58.750
[grunts]

00:58.750 --> 01:00.750
Unless you want to go to jail,

01:00.750 --> 01:02.041
you'll do exactly what
we agreed to.

01:02.041 --> 01:03.709
[Lee] Andrew Finney
was in three hours ago

01:03.709 --> 01:05.709
telling the Chief of Police
you killed the guy.

01:05.709 --> 01:07.250
- Has he been arrested?
- I do know they're gonna

01:07.250 --> 01:09.500
want to talk to you
before they charge him.

01:09.500 --> 01:11.000
[Cochran] You're going down
for the one fucking murder

01:11.000 --> 01:12.625
you didn't commit.

01:12.625 --> 01:13.709
I mean,
that's divine retribution.

01:13.709 --> 01:15.000
Where's the poker?

01:15.000 --> 01:17.208
Fuck yourself,
you Irish piece of shit.

01:17.208 --> 01:18.834
Ahh! God!

01:18.834 --> 01:20.333
Where's the poker?

01:20.333 --> 01:22.000
- [pounding on door]
- Ray Donovan,

01:22.000 --> 01:24.917
we have a warrant
to search the premises.

01:27.750 --> 01:29.041
[tires screech]

01:29.041 --> 01:30.250
Tell the truth
and get it all.

01:30.250 --> 01:31.709
Who knows, you play
your cards right,

01:31.709 --> 01:33.125
you might even keep
the team.

01:33.125 --> 01:35.083
Why would your father
kill your husband?

01:35.083 --> 01:36.625
They were lovers.

01:54.542 --> 01:57.583
♪ tense music ♪

01:57.583 --> 01:59.542
[door opens]

01:59.542 --> 02:01.417
[footsteps approach]

02:06.166 --> 02:08.166
[door closes]

02:11.875 --> 02:13.625
Anyone see you come in?

02:13.625 --> 02:15.750
No.
I took the service entrance.

02:22.291 --> 02:25.208
I'll wait downstairs.

02:25.208 --> 02:27.166
Stay here.

02:27.166 --> 02:30.417
Keep out of the shit show
for a while.

02:30.417 --> 02:33.166
I'll get your PR people
to come by tomorrow.

02:36.917 --> 02:39.250
There are more helicopters
outside my dad's house

02:39.250 --> 02:43.542
than when OJ took
the white Bronco down the 405.

02:43.542 --> 02:45.250
Yeah.

02:50.125 --> 02:53.208
How they love to see
the mighty fall.

03:00.667 --> 03:03.333
You did the right thing,
Paige.

03:06.959 --> 03:09.000
Do you think that's a comfort?

03:12.375 --> 03:14.041
I don't know.

03:16.125 --> 03:18.208
Key's on the counter.

03:18.208 --> 03:20.917
You know, my father never
would have killed Varick

03:20.917 --> 03:22.959
if you weren't around.

03:22.959 --> 03:24.750
He fell in love with the idea

03:24.750 --> 03:26.417
that there was always
gonna be someone there

03:26.417 --> 03:28.375
to save him from himself.

03:31.041 --> 03:33.500
I'll have my girl check on you
in the morning.

03:38.041 --> 03:41.625
Are you sure you can't stay?

03:41.625 --> 03:46.417
♪

03:57.834 --> 03:59.250
[door closes]

04:13.125 --> 04:16.333
Santa Monica.
By the pier.

04:16.333 --> 04:18.208
[sniffles]

04:18.208 --> 04:20.667
I'll be at the Paradise Inn.

04:20.667 --> 04:23.375
Please hurry.
I'm really scared.

04:23.375 --> 04:28.417
♪

04:30.709 --> 04:33.417
Bridget?

04:33.417 --> 04:34.583
[knocking]

04:34.583 --> 04:36.291
Bridget?

04:42.208 --> 04:43.959
Bridge?

04:43.959 --> 04:49.041
♪

05:08.417 --> 05:10.417
Baby, wake up.

05:13.583 --> 05:14.917
Nene, wake up.

05:14.917 --> 05:16.917
Mm.

05:16.917 --> 05:18.458
[chuckles]

05:24.250 --> 05:26.000
I want to play.

05:29.291 --> 05:32.750
Come on.
I want to play.

05:36.583 --> 05:38.667
What are you doing?

05:47.166 --> 05:49.291
Don't you fucking speak
without my permission.

05:49.291 --> 05:51.792
Oh, shit.

05:51.792 --> 05:54.125
- Oh!
- Disobey me, you mariquita?

05:55.125 --> 05:57.250
Did you call me
a margarita?

05:57.250 --> 05:59.291
Say you're sorry, motherfucker,
or I'll pull it off.

05:59.291 --> 06:01.125
- I'm--I'm sorry.
- Huh?

06:01.125 --> 06:02.125
Louder.

06:02.125 --> 06:04.041
I'm sorry.

06:04.041 --> 06:06.542
- I bet you are.
- Ah.

06:11.792 --> 06:14.208
[both moaning]

06:17.333 --> 06:19.500
Oh.

06:22.125 --> 06:24.250
[both breathing heavily]

06:35.166 --> 06:37.500
Happy?

06:37.500 --> 06:39.500
Yeah.

06:43.250 --> 06:47.500
Then get up.
We're going out.

06:47.500 --> 06:50.166
It's the middle of the night.

06:50.166 --> 06:52.208
I'm taking you somewhere.

06:54.166 --> 06:55.792
Come on.

06:55.792 --> 06:57.542
Pants on, bitch.

06:59.291 --> 07:01.583
You're not gonna
want to miss this.

07:07.208 --> 07:08.250
[door closes]

07:08.250 --> 07:09.542
[dog barks]

07:09.542 --> 07:12.458
[woman on TV
speaking indistinctly]

07:15.709 --> 07:19.333
All in all, plenty of sunshine
and really clear skies.

07:19.333 --> 07:21.041
This is Darby Jackson

07:21.041 --> 07:23.500
with your Southern California
daily weather.

07:23.500 --> 07:25.834
[man on TV] Now,
back to tonight's top story.

07:25.834 --> 07:28.917
Police were dispatched
to media mogul Andrew Finney's

07:28.917 --> 07:31.000
Bel Air estate just hours ago

07:31.000 --> 07:34.083
after hearing reports of
a fire burning on the property.

07:34.083 --> 07:35.709
When investigators
arrived at the scene,

07:35.709 --> 07:37.417
they discovered that the blaze
contained the remains...

07:37.417 --> 07:38.875
Raymond.

07:38.875 --> 07:40.875
...of an unidentified
adult male.

07:40.875 --> 07:42.583
Sources are currently saying
the victim may have been

07:42.583 --> 07:43.917
an employee
of the Finney organi--

07:43.917 --> 07:45.834
[TV turns off]

07:45.834 --> 07:47.417
Where is everybody?

07:47.417 --> 07:52.000
Conor's at a friend's house,
and, uh...

07:52.000 --> 07:54.583
Abby's out looking
for Bridget.

07:54.583 --> 07:56.583
Why is she looking
for Bridget?

07:58.917 --> 08:01.500
Sit down--there's something
I got to tell ya.

08:08.917 --> 08:11.834
Bridget got involved
with someone at school.

08:11.834 --> 08:12.917
Who?

08:14.250 --> 08:15.792
Her math teacher.

08:17.625 --> 08:19.417
What the fuck
are you talking about?

08:23.375 --> 08:28.458
♪

08:42.458 --> 08:44.417
How'd you know
they were his drugs?

08:44.417 --> 08:45.959
Well, we found the bottle
in her purse,

08:45.959 --> 08:47.792
and the prescription
had his name on it.

09:03.375 --> 09:05.667
Are ya all right?

09:07.125 --> 09:09.375
[liquor pours]

09:11.250 --> 09:13.083
How long have you known
about this?

09:13.083 --> 09:15.166
A few days.

09:15.166 --> 09:16.875
Few days, huh?

09:16.875 --> 09:18.500
Yeah, we talked about it,
and--

09:18.500 --> 09:19.917
You're not my kid's father,
Terry.

09:19.917 --> 09:21.625
No, but we thought
it was all under control.

09:21.625 --> 09:24.250
You keep fucking saying "we."
Wh--you and Abby?

09:24.250 --> 09:26.291
Huh?

09:26.291 --> 09:27.542
What's going on, Terry?

09:27.542 --> 09:29.500
You got a little crush
on my wife?

09:31.291 --> 09:32.750
I know you're fucked up
in the head,

09:32.750 --> 09:34.583
but don't get confused
about that, all right?

09:34.583 --> 09:35.959
I'm not the one
that's confused, Ray.

09:35.959 --> 09:37.000
You're the one
that don't get it.

09:37.000 --> 09:38.333
Don't get what?

09:38.333 --> 09:40.000
It's a disgrace
the way you treat her.

09:40.000 --> 09:41.875
You're out all night. You're
cheating like the old man did.

09:41.875 --> 09:43.500
- What?
- Yeah, you heard what I said!

09:43.500 --> 09:45.166
Stop it.

09:45.166 --> 09:47.709
Just both of you
fucking stop it.

09:47.709 --> 09:49.875
[sets keys on counter]

09:52.959 --> 09:54.458
Why'd you keep this from me?

09:54.458 --> 09:57.333
Because I knew you'd go
fucking nuts.

09:57.333 --> 09:59.208
That's not your decision
to make.

09:59.208 --> 10:01.083
She's my fucking daughter.

10:02.750 --> 10:04.208
I know how you handle things.

10:04.208 --> 10:05.750
What the fuck is that
supposed to mean?

10:05.750 --> 10:07.250
It means you have problems
with shit like this.

10:07.250 --> 10:08.834
Oh, yeah?
Until you come face-to-face

10:08.834 --> 10:11.000
with something ugly and you
need me to make it go away.

10:11.000 --> 10:12.500
I think what Abby's
trying to say--

10:12.500 --> 10:14.000
[shouting]
Do I need you to tell me

10:14.000 --> 10:16.542
what my fucking wife
is saying, huh?

10:16.542 --> 10:18.208
You got some kind of
inside line?

10:18.208 --> 10:19.625
No, he's just been here
helping me

10:19.625 --> 10:21.041
while you've been out
chasing Paige Finney.

10:21.041 --> 10:22.417
Fuck you.

10:22.417 --> 10:23.709
I want you
to pack your shit

10:23.709 --> 10:24.917
and get out of here
before I'm back.

10:24.917 --> 10:26.667
You're not going anywhere.

10:28.083 --> 10:29.750
It's not your decision.

10:29.750 --> 10:31.083
Where's he live?

10:31.083 --> 10:32.583
What?

10:32.583 --> 10:34.625
The teacher.
Where does he live?

10:37.583 --> 10:39.875
He's not home.
I was just there.

10:39.875 --> 10:42.083
Where does he live, Abby?

10:46.083 --> 10:47.500
Tell him.

10:49.583 --> 10:50.792
[sighs]

10:54.083 --> 10:57.792
[phone ringing]

11:28.250 --> 11:30.375
[dog barking]

11:59.333 --> 12:01.375
[Terry]
That was wrong.

12:01.375 --> 12:05.500
I shouldn't have talked
to him like that.

12:05.500 --> 12:07.417
He needed to hear it.

12:11.125 --> 12:13.000
I'm glad you said it.

12:15.166 --> 12:18.250
[phone chimes]

12:18.250 --> 12:20.875
It's her.
She's at Mickey's.

12:23.834 --> 12:26.125
You've been out all night.
I'll go get her.

12:26.125 --> 12:28.000
- I'll come with you.
- No. No.

12:28.000 --> 12:32.625
I don't want Ray thinking that
we are acting as a team.

12:32.625 --> 12:34.709
Now, when your husband
comes back,

12:34.709 --> 12:37.542
you are gonna talk

12:37.542 --> 12:39.959
and you're gonna
fix things.

12:41.709 --> 12:43.792
[phone ringing]

12:51.208 --> 12:52.208
Yeah?

12:52.208 --> 12:54.583
She's at Mickey's.

12:54.583 --> 12:56.542
Terry went to go
pick her up.

12:56.542 --> 12:58.875
I'll meet him there.

12:58.875 --> 13:02.333
You didn't have to be
so hard on him.

13:02.333 --> 13:04.625
He didn't do anything wrong.

13:07.834 --> 13:10.041
Ray, you there?

13:10.041 --> 13:11.709
Yeah.

13:11.709 --> 13:13.750
Look, just tell him
you didn't mean it.

13:13.750 --> 13:15.250
Tell him you don't
want him to leave.

13:16.542 --> 13:18.417
Otherwise he'll pack his bags,

13:18.417 --> 13:20.917
and he'll never come back.

13:22.750 --> 13:24.625
Is that what you want?

13:30.917 --> 13:32.083
Ray?

13:32.083 --> 13:33.375
I'll talk to him.

13:33.375 --> 13:34.917
[phone beeps]

13:37.208 --> 13:42.250
♪

13:45.834 --> 13:46.709
Oh.

13:46.709 --> 13:51.417
My beautiful,
beautiful boy.

13:51.417 --> 13:54.417
I missed you so much.

13:54.417 --> 13:57.458
Bring Davros some mantee.

13:57.458 --> 13:59.917
Prison food is shit.

13:59.917 --> 14:01.458
You want some bread
and pickles with that?

14:01.458 --> 14:02.667
Nah.

14:04.500 --> 14:08.333
It's true what Vartan
said about Mickey?

14:10.792 --> 14:12.959
Nothing is ever easy.

14:15.250 --> 14:16.291
Hmm.

14:22.417 --> 14:24.291
Mmm, it's good.

14:24.291 --> 14:26.208
[chuckles]

14:26.208 --> 14:29.500
They put enough sumac
for once.

14:33.333 --> 14:36.250
[pop music plays distantly]

14:36.250 --> 14:41.333
♪

14:43.500 --> 14:45.000
I'm sorry I stole the car.

14:45.000 --> 14:47.000
Uh, I don't know what
the hell I was thinking.

14:55.500 --> 14:57.709
I'm not worth it.

15:00.083 --> 15:02.083
My own mother hates me.

15:07.333 --> 15:09.667
Six, one thousand.

15:09.667 --> 15:11.625
Seven, one thousand.

15:11.625 --> 15:13.333
Eight, one thousand.

15:13.333 --> 15:16.041
Nine, one thousand.

15:16.041 --> 15:17.333
Ten, one thousand.

15:17.333 --> 15:19.000
[women whispering]

15:19.000 --> 15:21.875
All right, ready or not,
here I come.

15:21.875 --> 15:24.875
[music plays in background]

15:24.875 --> 15:26.709
One, two, three,
the coke shuffle.

15:26.709 --> 15:28.041
[laughter]

15:28.041 --> 15:29.542
You clever girls.

15:29.542 --> 15:31.166
Wonder where it could be.

15:31.166 --> 15:33.875
It's not over here.

15:33.875 --> 15:35.625
Doesn't seem to be over here.

15:35.625 --> 15:38.583
Oh, look what I found!

15:38.583 --> 15:40.291
I found it.

15:40.291 --> 15:41.667
You found coke?

15:41.667 --> 15:43.500
[indistinct chatter]

15:43.500 --> 15:45.500
Don't move.

15:45.500 --> 15:47.417
[phone ringing]

15:51.542 --> 15:52.917
Oh, fuck you, Ray.

15:52.917 --> 15:54.375
All right, now it's yours.
Go ahead.

15:54.375 --> 15:56.000
- I'm counting?
- Here's a straw.

15:56.000 --> 15:58.250
- You count, you guys hide.
- You're it.

15:58.250 --> 15:59.667
- I'm hiding it.
- You guys are hiding.

15:59.667 --> 16:01.041
Now, we hide it.

16:01.041 --> 16:02.333
[phone rings]

16:02.333 --> 16:03.959
Oh.

16:05.917 --> 16:09.166
Oh, time out.
I got to take this.

16:09.166 --> 16:12.000
Ahh.
Hello, sweetie pie.

16:12.000 --> 16:14.083
You all right?

16:14.083 --> 16:15.834
[Bridget]
I'm scared to go home.

16:15.834 --> 16:18.417
I told my mother
that I'm at your apartment.

16:18.417 --> 16:21.041
Oh?
What happened?

16:21.041 --> 16:22.709
Dad found out
about my new boyfriend,

16:22.709 --> 16:24.917
and he's gonna hurt him.

16:24.917 --> 16:27.083
Can you please tell them
that I'm there with you?

16:27.083 --> 16:30.542
Oh, if I do that,
he'd come right over.

16:30.542 --> 16:32.417
Come back and bite ya.

16:32.417 --> 16:33.583
[knock at door]

16:33.583 --> 16:34.917
Forget it.
Never mind.

16:37.500 --> 16:39.667
[knocking continues]

16:43.250 --> 16:44.417
Are you okay?

16:44.417 --> 16:47.583
No, I'm not.
It's not okay.

16:47.583 --> 16:49.959
My dad found out,
and he's gonna hurt you.

16:49.959 --> 16:52.291
Okay, Bridget, slow down.

16:52.291 --> 16:53.959
You don't know him,
okay?

16:53.959 --> 16:55.625
He can be
a very dangerous person.

16:55.625 --> 16:57.834
We need to leave Los Angeles.

16:57.834 --> 16:59.792
Leave Los Angeles?
Bridget, that's insane.

16:59.792 --> 17:01.792
Well, then you need
to stay here with me.

17:01.792 --> 17:03.125
In a hotel room with you?

17:03.125 --> 17:05.667
Yeah, that's gonna
calm everyone down.

17:05.667 --> 17:07.208
[sighs]
Okay, come on.

17:07.208 --> 17:10.792
Let's just--
let's go for a walk.

17:10.792 --> 17:12.291
Okay?
We'll think of something.

17:19.458 --> 17:22.792
I don't think you're supposed to
walk in the woods at night.

17:22.792 --> 17:24.792
Who says?

17:24.792 --> 17:28.166
There's snakes
and coyotes and shit.

17:28.166 --> 17:30.875
Pshh. They fuck with us,
they'll have a problem.

17:34.166 --> 17:36.542
Well, how do you even know
about this place?

17:36.542 --> 17:40.667
We used to smoke weed out here
when I was in high school.

17:40.667 --> 17:42.750
This is where I lost
my virginity.

17:42.750 --> 17:45.333
[siren wails in the distance]

17:45.333 --> 17:47.375
I didn't know Mexicans hiked.

17:49.166 --> 17:52.500
I'm gonna pretend you didn't
just fucking say that.

17:52.500 --> 17:54.333
[keys jingle]

18:01.000 --> 18:03.166
[dog barking]

18:06.458 --> 18:08.125
[knocking on door]

18:08.125 --> 18:11.208
[Al Wilson's "Show and Tell"
plays on stereo]

18:11.208 --> 18:12.709
[laughs]

18:14.792 --> 18:16.709
Terry!
What's going on, baby?

18:16.709 --> 18:18.041
Where's Bridget?

18:18.041 --> 18:19.709
What?
What do you mean?

18:19.709 --> 18:21.500
Why would Bridget be here?

18:21.500 --> 18:23.083
Terry!
Come on in.

18:23.083 --> 18:25.542
Take your pants off.

18:25.542 --> 18:27.208
[laughing]

18:27.208 --> 18:28.625
Is Bridget with you?

18:28.625 --> 18:30.458
I don't think so.

18:30.458 --> 18:31.959
♪ Show and tell ♪

18:31.959 --> 18:33.625
♪ Just a game I play... ♪

18:33.625 --> 18:36.709
Oh, shit.

18:36.709 --> 18:37.917
[dialing on phone]

18:37.917 --> 18:39.041
[Daryll]
What's up, man?

18:39.041 --> 18:41.000
Abby, I'm at Mick's.

18:41.000 --> 18:43.041
She's not here.
She must have lied.

18:43.041 --> 18:45.625
She called me.

18:45.625 --> 18:47.417
I'll call you back.

18:47.417 --> 18:48.625
- She called me.
- When?

18:48.625 --> 18:50.083
A few minutes ago.

18:50.083 --> 18:52.375
Wanted me
to cover for her.

18:52.375 --> 18:56.375
Something about Ray not
liking her new boyfriend.

18:56.375 --> 18:59.792
You should have told us, Mick.
You don't sit on shit like that.

18:59.792 --> 19:00.917
I can call her.

19:00.917 --> 19:03.417
See if she'll pick up for me.

19:03.417 --> 19:05.208
See if I can meet her somewhere.

19:05.208 --> 19:07.750
♪ That can't help
calling your name... ♪

19:07.750 --> 19:10.792
[exhales and sniffs]

19:30.917 --> 19:33.208
[music continues playing]

19:33.208 --> 19:36.125
She ain't answering.

19:36.125 --> 19:37.625
[both exhale]

19:37.625 --> 19:40.333
♪ Tell me that you feel
the same... ♪

19:40.333 --> 19:42.959
Shit!
Mick, get down!

19:42.959 --> 19:44.291
Aah!

19:45.750 --> 19:47.291
